@startuml 09A-sequence-candidate-assessment
' CVerify — Candidate assessment (Pipeline Line 2), trigger -> queue -> AI DAG -> persistence -> SSE.
' Verified against:
'   Modules/Profiles/Controllers/CandidateAssessmentController.cs
'       TriggerAssessment:90-98 · GetProgressStream:229-348 (SSE) · dev-trigger:114-128 [AllowAnonymous]
'   Modules/Profiles/Services/CandidateAssessmentService.cs
'       TriggerAssessmentAsync:166-234 (concurrency check:177, readiness:186, insert:199-216,
'                                       CreateSessionAsync:219, EnqueueAssessmentAsync:231)
'       ProcessAssessmentJobAsync:304-928 (CancelAfter 10 min:308, Redis lock:326-336,
'                                       repo assess loop:393-493, /repository/assess:443,
'                                       payload build:608-630, /candidate/assess/stream:633,
'                                       HMAC headers:641-646, SSE read loop:655-715,
'                                       artifact persist:709-712, CandidateProfile check:718-724)
'       PublishRawProgressAsync:966-970 (channel candidate:assessment:progress:{userId})
'   Modules/Profiles/Services/BackgroundCandidateAssessmentQueue.cs  (in-process singleton)
'   Modules/Profiles/BackgroundWorkers/BackgroundCandidateAssessmentProcessor.cs:27-70
'   Modules/Shared/System/Services/HmacSignatureService.cs
'   CVerify.AI/app/api/routes/analysis_router.py:89 (/api/v1/candidate/assess/stream)
'   CVerify.AI/app/pipelines/candidate/orchestrate_stream.py:14-31 (STAGES), :306-388 (execution loop)
'   CVerify.AI/app/pipelines/candidate/orchestrator.py:89-90 (PipelineDAG + validate)
' Ground truth: GROUND-TRUTH.md §5.3, §5.4, §6.2 (Line 2 = 16-task validated DAG).

title CVerify — Candidate Assessment (POST api/v1/candidate-assessments)

skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam maxMessageSize 280

actor       "Candidate"                                   as U
participant "Next.js Client"                              as C
participant "CandidateAssessmentController"               as CT
participant "CandidateAssessmentService"                  as SVC
participant "BackgroundCandidateAssessmentQueue\n<<singleton, in-process>>" as Q
participant "BackgroundCandidateAssessmentProcessor\n<<IHostedService>>"    as W
participant "HmacSignatureService"                        as HMAC
participant "CVerify.AI\nanalysis_router"                 as AI
participant "CandidateAssessmentStreamOrchestrator"       as ORCH
participant "Anthropic Claude"                            as CLAUDE
database    "PostgreSQL"                                  as DB
database    "Redis"                                       as R

== Trigger ==
U  -> C  : "Run assessment"
C  -> CT : POST /api/v1/candidate-assessments  (cookie auth)
CT -> SVC : TriggerAssessmentAsync(userId)
SVC -> DB : any assessment in Queued|Running?
alt already active
    SVC --> C : 400 ASSESSMENT_ALREADY_ACTIVE
end
SVC -> SVC : GetReadinessStatusAsync
alt not ready
    SVC --> C : 400 PROFILE_INCOMPLETE\n(at least one analyzed repo linked to the CV)
end
SVC -> DB : INSERT CandidateAssessment\n(Status=Queued, Version=max+1,\nPipelineVersion 2.2.0, CvId = UserId)
note right of SVC
  `CvId = userId` is a deliberate placeholder — there is no `cvs`
  table in the schema, so `candidate_assessments.CvId` has no real
  target (GROUND-TRUTH §4.1 hazard 6, marked <<Not verified>>).
end note
SVC -> DB : AiStreamingSession (pipelineId "candidate-assessment")
SVC -> Q  : EnqueueAssessmentAsync(assessmentId)
CT --> C  : 202 Accepted { id, status: Queued }

note over Q #ffdddd
  **The queue is a singleton in-process channel — not durable**
  (GROUND-TRUTH §5.4). If the API process restarts, queued
  candidate-assessment jobs are lost. Unlike the repository
  pipeline there is no equivalent of `AnalysisQueueRecoverySweeper`
  for this queue, so the row simply stays "Queued" forever.
end note

== Background execution ==
W  -> Q  : DequeueAssessmentAsync()  (1 s idle delay)
W  -> SVC : ProcessAssessmentJobAsync(assessmentId)  (scoped DI)
SVC -> SVC : linked CTS, CancelAfter(10 min)
SVC -> R  : LockTakeAsync candidate:assessment:lock:{userId} (10 min)
alt lock not acquired
    SVC --> W : abandon silently (job left Queued)
end
SVC -> DB : Status = Running
SVC -> R  : publish progress {Running, Initialize, 0%}

group Per-repository pre-assessment (max 5 CV-linked repos)
    SVC -> DB : ProjectRepositoryLinks + completed AnalysisJobs
    loop for each selected AnalysisJob
        alt cached RepositoryAssessment with matching\npipeline/model/prompt/schema version exists
            SVC -> DB : reuse existing assessment
        else
            SVC -> HMAC : CreateSignatureHeaders("POST", "/api/v1/repository/assess", body)
            SVC -> AI  : POST /api/v1/repository/assess\nX-Client-Id, X-Timestamp, X-Nonce,\nX-Correlation-Id = assessmentId, X-Signature
            AI  --> SVC : complexityScore, qualityScore, primaryLanguages,\nverifiedPatterns, cloneRiskClassification
            SVC -> DB : RepositoryAssessment = Completed
        end
    end
end

SVC -> DB : load profile, skills, experiences,\neducations, certifications, projects
SVC -> HMAC : CreateSignatureHeaders("POST", "/api/v1/candidate/assess/stream", body)
SVC -> AI  : POST /api/v1/candidate/assess/stream\n{ cv, repositoryAssessments, backgroundRepositories }\n(HttpCompletionOption.ResponseHeadersRead)

== 16-task candidate DAG (AI service) ==
AI -> ORCH : orchestrate_async(cv, repositoryAssessments, correlation_id)
ORCH --> SVC : data: {Running, FetchLine1, 5%}
ORCH --> SVC : data: {Running, ConsolidateLine1, 10%}
note over ORCH
  Roots L2-001, L2-007, L2-008, L2-011; sink L2-015.
  `PipelineDAG.validate()` runs at orchestrator construction:
  topological sort (cycle detection), PipelineContext schema
  check on every input_keys/output_keys, and an unused-output scan.
  L2-004/005/006/009/010 are **hybrid** — a deterministic result
  overwrites the LLM's answer after the Claude call returns.
end note
note over ORCH #ffdddd
  Surprise: although the DAG is built and validated,
  `orchestrate_stream.STAGES` executes the 16 tasks
  **sequentially from a hard-coded list**, not from the
  topological order the DAG computed. The DAG therefore acts
  as a compile-time validator, not as the runtime scheduler,
  and no task-level parallelism is exploited.
end note

loop for each of the 16 stages L2-001 … L2-015
    ORCH --> SVC : data: {Running, L2-0xx, pct}
    ORCH -> CLAUDE : stream=True, max_tokens=8192,\nprompt caching cache_control: ephemeral
    CLAUDE --> ORCH : JSON (json_repair fallback on malformed output)
    ORCH -> ORCH : merge result_data back into `inputs`\n(accumulative context, no re-fetch)
    ORCH --> SVC : data: {Completed, L2-0xx, artifactType, jsonData,\ninputTokens, outputTokens, costUsd, modelName}
    SVC -> DB  : UpdateSessionProgress / UpsertStage / AddLog / AddMetric
    SVC -> DB  : SaveOrUpdateArtifactAsync(assessmentId, artifactType, jsonData)
    SVC -> R   : PUBLISH candidate:assessment:progress:{userId}  (camelCase payload)
    alt stage status == Failed
        SVC -> DB : FailedStage / FailureReason
        SVC -> R  : publish {Failed, step, 100%}
        SVC --> W : throw — pipeline aborted
    end
end
ORCH --> SVC : data: [DONE]

== Persistence & completion ==
SVC -> DB : read CandidateAssessmentArtifacts where ArtifactType = "CandidateProfile"
alt artifact missing
    SVC --> W : throw "Final CandidateProfile artifact was not found"
end
SVC -> SVC : enforce schemaVersion ∈ {candidate-profile-v2, candidate-profile-v3}
SVC -> DB : ProjectRelationalDataAsync / SaveCandidateRelationalProfileAsync\n/ SaveCandidateSkillTreeAsync
SVC -> DB : Status = Completed, CompletedAtUtc
SVC -> R  : publish {Completed, CandidateProfileComposer, 100%}
SVC -> R  : LockRelease candidate:assessment:lock:{userId}

== SSE progress channel (parallel to the whole flow) ==
C  -> CT : GET /api/v1/candidate-assessments/progress/{userId}
CT -> CT : reject with 403 if userId != CurrentUserId
CT -> DB : GetFormattedHistoryAsync(assessmentId) — replay past events
CT --> C : data: <historical events>
alt session already terminal (Completed|Failed|Cancelled)
    CT --> C : data: [DONE]
end
CT -> R  : SUBSCRIBE candidate:assessment:progress:{userId}
CT -> DB : re-check status after subscribing (race guard)
loop until terminal status or client disconnect
    R  --> CT : live event
    CT -> CT : drop event whose timestamp <= last replayed timestamp
    CT --> C : data: <event>
end
CT --> C : data: [DONE]
CT -> R  : UNSUBSCRIBE

note over C, CT
  GROUND-TRUTH §8: the client's streaming store appends a `token`
  query parameter read from localStorage/sessionStorage for SSE,
  diverging from the HttpOnly-cookie auth used everywhere else.
  nginx access logs (shipped to Cloud Logging) would then contain
  the token. Whether that key is ever populated is <<Not verified>>.
end note

@enduml
